    <subfield code="y">00000 Computed modulated electron spectra at Earth (with polar angle of $\theta = 90^{\circ}$) at 90 AU and 110 AU (with $\theta = 60^{\circ}$ corresponding to the Voyager 1 trajectory), showing how they are modulated from the inner to the outer heliosphere. These spectra are completely compatible to observations from Voyager 1 during 2010, PAMELA during 2009 [5,6,7,8,9], and from Ulysses as observed in 1997 [12]. This very LIS is specified at the heliopause positioned at 120 AU. See also [1,14].</subfield>
  </datafield>
