    <subfield code="y">00001 A comparison between the electron LIS reported here (solid black line) and a LIS (dash line in red) with a spectral index of $âˆ’(3.13\pm0.05)$ above 2 GeV and normalized to the PAMELA data above 30 GeV. The preliminary PAMELA electron intensities from November 2006 are presented by the symbols. At lower energies the LIS from [1] is used. Note that data between $\sim$2 GeV and $\sim$10 GeV, perhaps even 20 GeV, requires a different spectral slope than above 30 GeV.</subfield>
